Title : Fo Guang Shan Temple, Toronto
Text : {{Use dmy dates|date=July 2019}}
'''Fo Guang Shan Temple''' is a [[Buddhist]] temple of the [[Mahayana]] monastic order in [[Mississauga, Ontario]]. Its is the only Canadian branch of [[Fo Guang Shan]] from [[Taiwan]]. The temple features a prayer hall and tea house<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thestar.com/life/2009/05/27/temple_offers_tea_and_tranquility.html|title=Temple offers tea and tranquility - The Star|publisher=|accessdate=12 August 2018}}</ref> on the ground floor, a library and museum on the second floor, and a meeting hall and rooms on the lower floor. The building is opened to the public year round, although prayer areas are closed during prayer service on Mondays.

A secondary temple was opened in [[Thornhill, Ontario|Thornhill]] in 1999 (later relocated to [[Markham, Ontario|Markham]] in 2002) to offer facilities to members in the [[York Region]] who may not be able to travel to the Mississauga site.<ref>{{cite web |title=Markham Buddhist Light Centre |url=http://www.english.fgs2.ca/?q=markham-buddhâ€™s-light-centre |accessdate=12 August 2018}}</ref>

